CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 15, 1958, pg. 24, reads: "Bob Castelberry...game is improving - Harris photo." Portions of accompanying article read: "...Bob Castelberry, who never rolled a tenpin ball before last September, is now sporting a 150 average. He is a member of the Eagle Linen League, which he organized last summer.  They roll every Friday at 9:30..."
TitMainTitle: Bob Castelberry lifting bowling ball from rack, possibly in Meadow Lanes bowling alley with sign inscribed "Please Observe Foul Line"
